			<h2><strong>4.</strong> About</h2><a name='about' />
			<h3>Green is Good is written and produced by Matt Wood.</h3>
			<p>
				I am currently the head of Production Software at the <a href='http://www.sanger.ac.uk'>Wellcome Trust 
				Sanger Institute</a>, a genomic research facility in <a href='http://maps.google.co.uk/maps?f=q&source=s_q&hl=en&geocode=&q=cambridge&sll=52.023292,0.243034&sspn=0.110066,0.222816'>Cambridge, UK</a>.
			</p>
			<p>
				Previously, I've built grid computers in <a href='http://www.nottingham.ac.uk'>Nottingham</a>, web scale <a href='http://www.twease.org'>search tools</a> in <a href='http://www.cornell.edu/'>New York City</a> and <a href='http://www.ensembl.org'>genes in Hinxton</a>.
			</p>
